column1: Multiplication result converted to larger type
column2: A multiplication result that is converted to a larger type can be a sign that the result can overflow the type converted from.
column4: Multiplication result may overflow 'unsigned int' before it is converted to '__off_t'.

column2: An allocated memory block is used after it has been freed. Behavior in such cases is undefined and can cause memory corruption.
column4: Memory may have been previously freed by [["call to g_free"|"relative:///src/mbuf.c:113:13:113:18"]].
